text: Te Kūiti is a town in the northern part of the King Country. It is located approximately 80 kilometers south of Hamilton and 19 kilometers south of Ōtorhanga on State Highway 3 and State Highway 30. It has four primary schools and one high school situated within the town. It is the home of All Black great Colin Meads. ==References== Category:Towns in Waikato Category:Waitomo District
title: Te Kūiti
